C++ also supportsinput manipulators, which alter the way that input is accepted. Thestd::wsinput manipulator tellsstd::cinto ignore any leading whitespace before extraction. Leading whitespace is any whitespace character (spaces, tabs, newlines) that occur at the start of the string.Let’s explore why this is useful. Consider the following program:#include <iostream>
#include <string>

